                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="12716093" author="pwolanin" created="Wed, 3 Jun 2009 23:47:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a simple patch that follows the pattern in the other core admin methods.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12716170" author="noble.paul" created="Thu, 4 Jun 2009 07:23:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;it should throw an exception if the core does not exist&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12716171" author="noble.paul" created="Thu, 4 Jun 2009 07:24:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;committed revision: 781656&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12716252" author="pwolanin" created="Thu, 4 Jun 2009 13:11:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Do we need to open another issue (maybe for 1.5) - I&apos;d think the expected behavior would be to throw a specific exception anywhere in core admin that a core is not found, and then catch it and return a 404?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the moment, however, you can request status for a non-existent core, etc, and get a 200 with some data, so this patch makes the behavior consistent, at least.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12716255" author="noble.paul" created="Thu, 4 Jun 2009 13:18:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;If a core does not exist &apos;unload&apos;ing that core is not possible . So it is an error. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For status command. it would be better to return &quot;no such  core exists&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775762" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:52:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
